title: Loan Payment (PMT) Calculator
formula_js: (inputs) => { const r = (inputs.rate/100)/12; const n = inputs.months; const pv = inputs.principal; const pmt = r===0 ? pv/n : (r*pv)/(1-Math.pow(1+r,-n)); return { result: Number(pmt.toFixed(2)), steps: [`Monthly rate r = ${(inputs.rate/100)/12}`, `Payment = r*PV / (1-(1+r)^-n)`] }; }
intro: Estimate your fixed monthly loan payment using the standard annuity formula.

faqs.a: We use PMT = r×PV / (1−(1+r)^(−n)) with a monthly rate.
